OL,3,CIt's a Merry Christmas for Wales'
OL,4,COldest man after receiving trolley of
OL,5,Cgifts
OL,7,FMr Filer says he puts his longevity to
OL,8,F"never really growing up" as well as
OL,9,Fhaving a thimble of Scotch before bed.
OL,10,FReacting to his presents, Mr Filer
OL,11,Fsaid that everyone knows his name at
OL,12,Fthe store and are really friendly.
OL,14,F"I always have a good chat and a laugh
OL,15,Fand a joke, and if I need help with
OL,16,Fanything I'll always get it."
OL,18,FMr Filer has four children, 10
OL,19,Fgrandchildren and 15 great-
OL,20,Fgrandchildren, with the youngest being
OL,21,Fthree months old.
